chunk_content: Ideally, data for this indicator should be collected from an electronic medical records system (EMR) to 173 minimize data collection errors and ensure that results are informing patient care. If data collection from an EMR is not possible, indicator data may be collected from paper-based registers or reports that reflect the VL results. If standard patient registers do not contain all the required information, V I individual patient records should be reviewed. R A If a clinical source does not exist or does not contain the desired information, data may be extracted L from an electronic laboratory information system (LIS). VL results from an LIS must be linked to back S U to the individual patients and their record at sites. P P NOTE: If patient-linked VL results from LIS are used for reporting, it is incumbent that the R implementing partner ensure this information is transcribed into the patient record for timely VL E results utilization/patient management.
